[7] Australia (Queensland) ex Samoa
Date: Wed 4 Dec 2019 7:05 AM AEST
Source: Perth Now, The Courier-Mail report [abridged, edited]
https://www.perthnow.com.au/news/qld/qld-headed-for-worst-measles-year-so-far-in-the-21st-century-as-three-new-cases-are-diagnosed-ng-a9e6f45827661689b6763640f00fcc73


Three new cases linked to outbreak in Samoa that has killed 60 and infected 4000

Qld headed for worst measles year so far in the 21st Century as 3 new cases are diagnosed

Three new measles cases -- linked to the outbreak in Samoa that has killed 60 and infected 4000 -- have been diagnosed in Queensland, taking the state's 2019 tally to 67, meaning 2019 will be the worst for diagnoses of the disease since 1997.

The 3 new cases, all from the one family, have been diagnosed by the West Moreton Hospital and Health Service.

Those cases are believed to be linked to the highly contagious virus being brought into Queensland by a person travelling from Samoa.

The Pacific nation's measles epidemic has been exacerbated by low vaccination rates.

Queensland's worst year for measles since 1997, when 267 people were diagnosed, was in 2014, when 72 cases were recorded.

But with the New Year still more than 3 weeks away, 2019 appears headed towards eclipsing 2014 as the state's worst year for measles in the 21st Century to date.

[Byline: Janelle Miles]

